{"updated_at": "2011-10-08T23:12:05Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2011-10-08T23:12:05Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2334308", "id": 2334308, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3256", "issue_id": 3256, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/jeremy", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "24d2f8804e6bb4b7ea6bd11e0a586470", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/24d2f8804e6bb4b7ea6bd11e0a586470?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F84d9ee44e457ddef7f2c4f25dc8fa865.png", "id": 199, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/events{/privacy}", "login": "jeremy", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/followers"}, "body": "This is embedding a view concern (how to name links) in your models, though.\r\n\r\nYou can just as easily keep that responsibility in a helper:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\ndef link_model(record)\r\n  link_to record.name, record\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nor in a presenter:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nclass FooView\r\n  def initialize(record, view)\r\n    ...\r\n  end\r\n\r\n  def anchor\r\n    view.link_to anchor_text, record\r\n  end\r\n\r\n  def anchor_text\r\n    record.name\r\n  end\r\nend\r\n```", "_id": {"$oid": "523838dbbd3543c15101004c"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3256#issuecomment-2334308"}
